10.03.2008 r2d22k
-fixed many small things, corrected stuff here and there, dont know if the following list is really complete
-introduced the transaction id, 03xx1fxx2513 packets use it
-added mapid where missing inside some packets
-corrected some things during first sync but its not completely right yet
-added a new helper server.tools.ExtendedByteArrayOutputStream
-implemented a partial working inventory! it wont save items yet and you cant fully customize the items also
 most checks are still missing and have to be implemented a command to spawn items in your inv has been added
 its described in the readme file
-added server.database.items.{Item, ItemContainer, ItemInfo, ItemInfoManager, ItemManager}
 the ItemInfoManager reads the items.def file from your NC2 dir and stores the needed information in ItemInfo
 objects. most of the information is not used yet
 ItemManager coordinates itemcreation movement and all that stuff
-added server.database.playerCharacter.inventory.{PlayerGogu, PlayerInventory, PlayerQB} the Gogu
 is just a placeholder, but the Inventory and QB are at least partially implemented(especially checks are
 still missing!)
-added the following packets clientside: InsideF2InvMove, InventoryCombineItems, InventoryMove
 the first one is used when the client move items in the f2 inv
 the second one is used when the player tries to combine items
 the third one is used when the player moves items between different parts of the inventory(qb f2) and when
 the player tries to move an item in the qb
-added following packets serverside: AddItem, InventoryMoveAck, InventoryMoveDenied
 the first one is used to add a new item to the inv
 the second one acknowledges itemmoves(seems like simple inventory moves in F2 inv dont have to be acked)
 the third one denies an itemmove

13.09.2007 r2d22k
-a small bugfix release, to prevent deadlocks in player class

06.08.2007 r2d22k
-just a small update to correct some mistakes in the code

29.07.2007 r2d22k
-added a small gui, you can enable it via the option "GUI" in the irata.cfg file, currently its just
 for development purposes
-if you start the server via the gui and shut it down via the shutdown button in the gui, the database
 will be saved correctly
-changed PlayerCharacter class. added "orientation" "tilt" and "status" to the misclist and added the
 corresponding static final ints, to represent the orientation(n-e-s-w), the tilt(up-mid-down) and the
 status (running, walking, standing) of a player
-modified the WorldManager so you wont get a nullpointer exception anymore if a wrong "int location" is given
 to getWorldname
-changed some thinks in ChatManager, but its still not working properly
-the Gameserver now inits the ZoneManager and stops it
-a class representing NPCs has been added
-the player class now holds the mapId and it (un)registers correctly at zones
-modified Zone class:
	* players, items and NPCs are now represented by TreeMaps, to faciliate working with mapIds
	* added a String representing the Worldname
	* the ZoneId is also saved directly in the Zone
	* a method getNPC has been added, so you can get NPCs via their worldId
	* the localChat method now sends the messages to all the players in the Zone
	* the registerplayer method checks for the first unused mapId
	* addNPCtoZone adds a new NPC to the Zone
	* sendNPCsinZone() sends all the NPCs currently in a Zone to the players currently in that Zone
	* sendNPCsinZone(Player pl) sends all the NPCs currently in a Zone to one specific player pl
	* sendNPCinZone sends the specified NPC to the specified player
	* sendPlayersPosinZone(pl) sends the PlayerPositionUpdate of all the Players in the zone to pl 
	* sendPlayersinZone(pl) sends the players currently in a Zone to one player
	* sendnewPlayerinZone(pl) sends the new player pl to the others
	* sendPlayerMovement(pl) sends the movement of pl to the others
-many things were changed in the ZoneManager. it now takes care of initializing zones
-the GamePacketReaderUDP has been modified, so it takes care of the new packets
-after syncing to a Zone it looks like the player updates are send after the TimeSync,
 so GetTimeSync calls pl.getZone().sendPlayersinZone(pl);  and  pl.getZone().sendnewPlayerinZone(pl);
-LocalChat now sends the messages directly to the Zone and a new command has been added "npc"
-Movement now saves the status, tilt and orientation of a player, too
-RequesInfoAboutWorldID has been added. The client sends this one if it wants to know more about a NPC,
 which has been sent before by SendPresentWorldID
-RequestPlayerNamebyPlayerId, gets called when the player wants to know its own name
-RequestShortPlayerInfo, requests the Name of a specific mapId
-an event has been added in SyncUDP to take care of sending the NPCs when a player comes into a zone
-the Location gets the locationstring directly from the zone
-forcedZoning isnt working anymore, gonna have a look into that...
-LocalChatMessage has got a new constructor. the new one also wants a mapId, so the client cant identify the
 sender of the message
-LongPlayerInfo has been added. it sends information(model, baserank, fraction, sl,...) about a
 playercharacter to a player
-PlayerPositionUpdate has to be send once before the LongPlayerInfo packet it sends some info about pos, tilt
 and orientation of one playercharacter to another player
-PositionUpdate has been modified, so the correct mapId is being sent
-SendPlayerNamebyPlayerId is the answar to RequestPlayerNamebyPlayerId
-SendPresentWorldID sends the position and the map ids of npcs to the players
-ShortPlayerInfo is the answer to RequestShortPlayerInfo
-SMovement sends the movement of a playercharacter to another player
-SZoning1 has been modified, so the correct mapId is being sent
-TestPack and TestPack03 are just for development purposes
-UDPAlive has been modified to send the correct mapId
-UpdateModel has been modified to send the correct mapId
-WorldNPCInfo sends information about a specific NPC, is the answer to RequestInfoAboutWorldID

